                                                                <div data-widget-id="wid__text__5f4e4cee46468" class="moto-widget moto-widget-text moto-preset-default  moto-spacing-top-small moto-spacing-right-auto moto-spacing-bottom-large moto-spacing-left-auto  " data-widget="text" data-preset="default" data-spacing="sala" data-visible-on="mobile-v" data-animation="">
                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Surely He has borne our griefs and carried our sorrows; yet we esteemed Him stricken; smitten by God, and afflicted. But He was wounded for our transgressions, He was bruised for our iniquities; The chastisement for our peace was upon Him, And by His stripes we are healed.  <b>Isaiah 53: 4-5</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“The LORD your God in your midst, The Mighty One, will save; He will rejoice over you with gladness, He will quiet you with His love, He will rejoice over you with singing.””
                                                                            <b>Zephaniah 3:17 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">How can one attempt to give understanding of God’s love as it really is incomprehensible.  God is enveloped in love and all that is done by God comes from His heart of love in the purest sense. Again, incomprehensible.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We must once again go back to the garden of Eden on that day when darkness and sin entered into the heart and soul of mankind.   In all of God’s creation the human race stands alone in being made in “the image of God”.  All else has His fingerprint and footprint on it, but we are made in His image.  Can we come to understand why Satan who is full of pride and wanted to dethrone God would come after mankind to pierce the heart of God?
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Ahh!  God is who He says He is yesterday today and forever.  There is no plan or scheme that the Lord God Almighty does not know of and that He doesn’t already have the answer proposed and carried out in eternity.  Just as He did in Eden.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We can research until the end of time and beyond and we will never find a comment or statement from Christ that describes His taking our griefs and our sorrows upon Himself, stricken and smitten because of our transgressions and bruised for our iniquities as a complaint or burden.  He willingly suffered and died. He has never been quoted as saying “that was a horrific ordeal, I’m glad it is over”, or anything to the contrary.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Jesus Christ received upon Himself from our Father ALL the guilt and wrath our sin deserves...satisfying the wrath of God for us.  In His last breath on the cross He said “It is finished!” And bowing His head, He gave up His spirit.”  In that moment of time the pure image of God is taken back from the hand of Satan and given back to those who would believe in Jesus for who He was, and is and forever shall be.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10"><b>THAT IS GOD’S LOVE...</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Zephaniah tells us He rejoices over us with gladness.  He looks from heaven and sees the blood of His Son has washed over us restoring us back to His image.  He quiets us with His love and rejoices once again that we are His people.  Let’s meditate on this passage and allow God’s pure love to permeate us today and for always.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10"><b>ABBA Father</b> this is your day, You call us to rejoice and be glad in it.  As we take today to contemplate Your love for us, may You check our hearts in those areas where we are standoffish and bring clarity to the reason we hold your love at bay.  We ask You Holy Spirit to help us desire a deeper relationship coming into the place we experience your gladness and pure love to bring us to total surrendered to You.   That we might be used as vessels of honor to pour Your love out to others and they may come to know You.  All glory, honor and praise is yours now and forever, Amen.
                                                                        </p>
